erpretations of jihad vary. It is seen as being both defensive and aggressive by traditionalists; only defensive and mainly about moral improvement by progressive Muslims; and being insurrectionist, aggressive, eternal and justifying violence against civilians by radical Islamists. One purpose of the book is to understand how the radical interpretation came to South Asia. The book also explains how theories about jihad are influenced by the political and social circumstances of the period and how these insights feed into practice legitimizing militant movements called jihad for that period.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aHadithxRelation to the Qurʼan. 0aIslamic fundamentalismzSouth Asia. 0aJihad.  aInterpretation.  aIslam.  aJihad.  aSouth Asia.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2020z978311069628808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020 Englishz978311070477808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2020z9783110704570oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831107170060 cprintz978311055039940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311071698640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110716986423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110716986/original  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1b2020  a978-3-11-069628-8  DG Ebook Package English 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020 